title: Trara Mountains
text:
The Trara mountain range is a mountainous region of <a href="Algeria">Algeria</a> located on the northwest coast of the country, with an average altitude of . It culminates at <a href="altitude">altitude</a> of at the level of the <a href="jebel%20Fellaoucene">jebel Fellaoucene</a>.
The Trara Mountains are a coastal range in the western extension of the <a href="Tell%20Atlas">Tell Atlas</a> mountains. It represents, in the Tell Oranais, a mountainous block whose access is very difficult. This <a href="massif">massif</a> appears as a mountainous arch between the <a href="Mediterranean%20Sea">Mediterranean Sea</a> to the <a href="north">north</a>, the valley of the Wadi Tafna to the east, the <a href="Wadi%20Mouilah">Wadi Mouilah</a> to the south and the valley of <a href="Wadi%20Kiss">Wadi Kiss</a> to the west which determines the <a href="Morocco">Moroccan</a> border.
This space represents a well-identified geographical entity in view of its rugged relief of east-west orientation running entirely north of the <a href="Wilayah">Wilayah</a> of <a href="Tlemcen%20Province">Tlemcen</a> and the northwest of the Wilayah of <a href="A%C3%AFn%20T%C3%A9mouchent%20Province">Aïn Témouchent</a>.
The <a href="vegetation">vegetation</a> of the massif is made up mainly of <a href="pine">pine</a>s and <a href="cypress">cypress</a>es.
